     Sept. 30 (Bloomberg) --An explosion and fire at a Nippon
Shokubai Co. plant in Himeji, western  Japan , yesterday left one
firefighter killed and 33 other people injured, according to
local police.  Among those hurt at the chemical makerâ€™s plant were 21
firefighters, 10 workers and two police officers, Hiroyuki
Ichimura, deputy commissioner at the Hyogo prefectural police,
said by phone today. There will be an investigation of the cause
of the incident, he said.  Nippon Shokubai officials will brief the press on the
accident at 2 p.m. local time today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
